        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 8:16PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 816 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Manter, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Richfield around 830 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southwestern
Kansas.</instruction>
